4. DQ GATE SCORING — Formula is wrong for real data
Confirmed in dq_gate.py lines 8–82:

Dimension	Formula	Bug
null_score	100 × (1 - avg_null_pct)²	Quadratic of column averages, not row-weighted
type_score	100 - (issue_count × 10)	10 issues = score 0, regardless of row count
dup_score	100 - (dup_count × 5)	Reads llm_hints.business_key_duplicate_count — if LLM enrichment hasn't run (it's async), dup_count = 0, score = 100 always
outlier_score	100 - (issue_count × 10)	Same issue-count-not-row-count problem
Fix (4 hours): Score each dimension as (clean_rows / total_rows) × 100. You already have null_percentage per column and row_count per dataset — these are the right inputs. An issue affecting 2 rows in 100,000 should not score the same as one affecting 50,000.

