13. JOB STORE — Confirmed race condition in claim_next_job
Confirmed in jobs_store.py lines 144–165:

python

row = conn.execute("SELECT job_id ... WHERE status='queued' LIMIT 1").fetchone()
# ← another thread can read the same row here
conn.execute("UPDATE jobs SET status='running' WHERE job_id=?", (job_id,))
SELECT-then-UPDATE without a transaction lock. Two workers can double-claim the same job.

Also: session_store._connect() sets PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL but jobs_store._connect() does NOT. Inconsistency confirmed.

Fix:

python

# Atomic claim using BEGIN IMMEDIATE
conn.execute("BEGIN IMMEDIATE")
row = conn.execute("SELECT job_id FROM jobs WHERE status='queued' ORDER BY created_at LIMIT 1").fetchone()
if row:
    conn.execute("UPDATE jobs SET status='running', updated_at=? WHERE job_id=?", (time.time(), row[0]))
conn.execute("COMMIT")
