16. FRONTEND STATE MANAGEMENT — 29 useState calls, no shared cache
Confirmed in EtlGenerationPanel.tsx lines 177–232: 29 useState calls managing plan, planRows, preview, manualReviewItemsState, phase1Code, phase2Code, sqlQualityScore, duckdbDiff, and more — all derived from one backend session, all managed independently.

lib/ directory confirmed: Contains only backend-bridge.ts, azure-agent.ts, assessmentDisplay.ts. No shared data fetching layer. Each component re-fetches independently.

Consequence: When applyManualResolutions resolves and updates the plan, preview and manualReviewItemsState are not invalidated — they still show pre-resolution data until manually refreshed.

Fix (pragmatic):

typescript

// lib/useSessionData.ts
export function useSessionData(sessionId: string) {
  const [cache, setCache] = useState<SessionCache>({});
  const invalidate = (key: keyof SessionCache) => setCache(prev => omit(prev, key));
  return { cache, invalidate };
}
All read-only views consume from this hook. All mutations call invalidate() on success.

